sentences: The group formed in Messina in 1967 as a beat group, and gradually moved to a more melodic style.
They became first known in 1968 for winning a musical contest, the Trofeo EuroDavoli with the song "In fondo al viale", which eventually was a sleeper hit and sold over 250,000 copies.
In 1969 their guitarist Gilberto Bruno, aged 23 years old, died in a car accident and was replaced by Mauro Culotta.

The same year they participated to the Cantagiro Festival, placing third with "In fondo al viale".
Between 1971 and 1972 the lead singer Filiberto "William" Ricciardi temporarily left the band, being replaced by Alberto Tadini, who recorded the singles "Lo schiaffo" and "Piccolo grande amore".
In 1972 the band got their major hit with the single "Per chi", a cover version of Badfinger's song "Without You".
The song won the bands competition at the 1972 Cantagiro Festival, and ranked #7 on the Italian hit parade.
The group briefly reformed in the early 1990s, with Enrico Bianchi replacing Ricciardi as lead vocalist.
